Hexagon lounge is a breathe of fresh air in this area. First, the space is beautiful with an amazing mural and is quickly becoming a neighborhood gem. Second, the staff is extremely attentive and approachable. The food is really good - this is a nice place to come for happy hour or grab dinner. Can't wait until they have brunch on the weekends. When the weather is nice, the front windows open up for a nice dining experience. Hexagon also hits the right price point for the neighborhood, unlike a number of new places that have opened. This will definitely be a regular spot for me.

The waitress brought us cups of ice w lemons, but there was no water in them...it took 15 extra minutes to get the water.  The food took 45 minutes to come out and sadly, it was awful. The spring rolls were overcooked and mushy on the inside. The "yuca" fries were not plain fried yuca as the menu stated. They were mixed with something with dairy in it and smelled strange. When I explained this to the waitress she said "Well, it's not like you didn't touch it.." and she refused to take it back. Next, she brought out the boneless buffalo wings. They were not battered and fried like all boneless wings I've ever seen. Instead, it looked like someone cut up a chicken breast, sauteed the peices in a pan and covered them in bbq sauce. This time, I did not eat even one and again, she refused to take it back. I was surprised to see all of these things on the bill totalling to $45.  Don't eat here. Save your money and go to Popeyes three blocks away.
